WEBVTT

00:01.130 --> 00:02.267
PREVIOUSLY
ON "VERONICA MARS"...

00:02.270 --> 00:03.623
STAY AWAY FROM THIS CASE.

00:03.630 --> 00:05.325
THIS IS MORE
THAN SOME OBSESSED SCHOOL KID.

00:05.330 --> 00:07.230
THAT'S REALLY COOL,
BUT ACTUALLY --

00:07.240 --> 00:08.696
I KNOW YOUR DAD,
YOU KNOW.

00:08.700 --> 00:11.305
MAYOR GOODMAN -- WHY DO YOU
WANT TO SCARE THAT GUY?

00:11.310 --> 00:13.608
YOU DON'T KNOW
WHAT HE REALLY IS.

00:15.640 --> 00:17.073
ENJOY CONFESSION.

00:17.080 --> 00:19.742
YOU WERE
IN THE CASINO THAT DAY?
I SAY IT'S LIKELY.

00:19.750 --> 00:22.719
TERRENCE OWES ME
A SIGNIFICANT AMOUNT OF MONEY.

00:22.720 --> 00:25.484
IT MIGHT BE HARD TO GET PAID
BY AN INCARCERATED MAN.

00:25.490 --> 00:28.914
THEY FOUND THE MURDER WEAPON
USED TO KILL LILLY --

00:28.920 --> 00:32.026
AARON'S OSCAR STATUE.

00:32.030 --> 00:36.126
IN 1987,
I WAS "PEOPLE" MAGAZINE'S

00:36.130 --> 00:37.768
"SEXIEST MAN ALIVE."

00:37.770 --> 00:40.238
I MADE A LOT OF MONEY
CHASING PEOPLE AROUND

00:40.240 --> 00:42.561
WITH MY SHIRT UNBUTI'ONED.

00:42.570 --> 00:48.133
IF I WANTED TO DO A MOVIE,
THE MOVIE GOT MADE.

00:48.140 --> 00:49.778
THEN I GOT OLDER.

00:49.780 --> 00:53.375
I STARTED GETTING CAST AS
THE FATHER OF SUPERSTAR TWEENS

00:53.380 --> 00:55.871
WHO HAVE NO IDEA WHO I AM.

00:55.880 --> 00:57.438
IT'S A NEW AGE.

00:57.450 --> 00:59.315
THEY'RE THE ONES WHO
ARE GE'I'I'ING MOVIES MADE TODAY.

00:59.320 --> 01:00.958
I'M JUST SOME OLD GUY.

01:00.960 --> 01:02.587
ENTER LILLY KANE --

01:02.590 --> 01:05.980
THIS YOUNG, BEAUTIFUL GIRL
WHO THOUGHT I HUNG THE MOON.

01:05.990 --> 01:10.199
IT'S A VERY POWERFUL THING
WHEN SOMEONE SEES YOU

01:10.200 --> 01:11.997
AS THE PERSON
THAT YOU WISH YOU WERE.

01:12.000 --> 01:17.199
EVEN IF THAT PERSON IS 16
AND DATING YOUR SON?

01:17.210 --> 01:19.770
I DIDN'T CLAIM
THAT IT WAS RIGHT.

01:19.780 --> 01:21.338
I SAID IT WAS POWERFUL.

01:21.340 --> 01:26.346
MR. ECHOLLS, DID YOU HAVE SEX
WITH LILLY KANE?

01:26.350 --> 01:30.912
NO, NO...
WE FOOLED AROUND A LITTLE,

01:30.920 --> 01:32.456
FOR LACK OF A BETTER TERM,

01:32.460 --> 01:34.314
BUT I NEVER HAD INTERCOURSE
WITH HER.

01:34.320 --> 01:35.787
AND YOU ENDED
THE RELATIONSHIP

01:35.790 --> 01:37.781
ON THE DAY SHE WAS KILLED,
CORRECT?

01:37.790 --> 01:39.018
YES.

01:39.030 --> 01:40.895
CAN YOU TELL US
WHAT HAPPENED?

01:40.900 --> 01:43.323
LILLY CAME TO THE HOUSE.

01:43.330 --> 01:46.367
SHE WANTED ATTENTION,
I GUESS.

01:46.370 --> 01:50.409
I TOLD HER WE HAD TO STOP.
SHE STORMED OUT.

01:50.410 --> 01:52.105
IT WASN'T
UNTIL AFTER SHE'D LEFT

01:52.110 --> 01:54.431
THAT I REALIZED
SHE HAD TAKEN MY OSCAR.

01:54.440 --> 01:56.340
SO I WENT TO HER HOUSE
TO GET IT BACK.

01:56.350 --> 01:58.238
AND DID SHE GIVE IT
TO YOU?

01:58.250 --> 02:01.674
NO. SHE YELLED A LOT.
SHE THREW AN ASHTRAY AT ME.

02:01.680 --> 02:05.480
THEN HER BROTHER, DUNCAN,
CAME OUT. HE WAS ENRAGED.

02:05.490 --> 02:07.549
HE WAS SCREAMING AT HER
ABOUT ME,

02:07.560 --> 02:11.257
I MEAN,
AS THOUGH I WASN'T EVEN THERE.

02:11.260 --> 02:13.956
I PROBABLY SHOULDN'T HAVE
LEFT HER WITH HIM,

02:13.960 --> 02:16.360
BUT I PANICKED.

02:16.370 --> 02:18.497
I MEAN,
AS CRAZY AS HE WAS ACTING,

02:18.500 --> 02:20.866
I NEVER
WOULD HAVE IMAGINED --

02:20.870 --> 02:22.064
OBJECTION.

02:22.070 --> 02:23.059
I'M SORRY, YOUR HONOR.

02:23.070 --> 02:24.708
SO, AFTER THIS ARGUMENT,

02:24.710 --> 02:28.373
THAT WAS THE LAST TIME
YOU SAW LILLY KANE?

02:28.380 --> 02:33.215
IT WAS THE LAST TIME
I SAW HER ALIVE, YES.

02:33.220 --> 02:35.711
SO, APPARENTLY, IF YOU'RE
HANDSOME AND FAMOUS ENOUGH,

02:35.720 --> 02:38.086
YOU CAN JUST LIE UNDER OATH,
AND THAT'S COOL.

02:38.090 --> 02:39.955
IT'S ALL
ABOUT THE TAPES NOW, HONEY.

02:39.960 --> 02:43.179
THAT OSCAR TROPHY WITH DUNCAN'S
HAIR IS GONNA CREATE DOUBT --

02:43.190 --> 02:45.181
REASONABLE OR OTHERWISE.

02:45.190 --> 02:47.055
BUT IF THEY BELIEVE
YOU AND LOGAN

02:47.060 --> 02:48.857
SAW AARON HAVING SEX
WITH LILLY,

02:48.860 --> 02:50.259
TH EY'LL CONVICT HIM.

02:50.270 --> 02:52.738
HONEY, WHEN YOU
GET YOUR CHANCE TO TESTIFY,

02:52.740 --> 02:55.493
IT'S IMPORTANT YOU KEEP YOURSELF
IN CHECK, OKAY?

02:55.500 --> 02:57.502
AARON'S LAWYER
IS GONNA USE EVERYTHING

02:57.510 --> 02:59.398
IN HIS BAG OF TRICKS
TO RILE YOU.

02:59.410 --> 03:03.301
BUT HERE'S THE THING --
I'M UN-RILE-ABLE.

03:03.310 --> 03:04.868
"EASYGOING VERONICA MARS" --

03:04.880 --> 03:06.609
THAT'S WHAT THE KIDS
AT SCHOOL CALL ME.

03:06.620 --> 03:09.316
YOU SURE YOU DON'T WANT TO
GO OVER YOUR TESTIMONY

03:09.320 --> 03:10.844
WITH THE LAWYERS AGAIN?

03:10.850 --> 03:14.513
YOU KNOW WHAT I WANT...
MORE THAN ANYTHING IN THE WORLD?

03:14.520 --> 03:18.229
I WANT TO BE THERE, IN COURT,
WATCHING AARON

03:18.230 --> 03:20.653
AT THE MOMENT
THE JURY READS THE VERDICT.

03:20.660 --> 03:23.663
I WANT TO SEE THAT SMIRK
WIPED FROM HIS FACE.

03:23.670 --> 03:26.662
I WANT TO SEE HIS EXPRESSION
AT THE EXACT MOMENT

03:26.670 --> 03:29.559
HE REALIZES HE'LL NEVER
BE A FREE MAN AGAIN.

03:29.570 --> 03:33.973
"EASYGOING VERONICA MARS,"
HUH?

03:35.780 --> 03:39.102
YOU KNOW HOW FAT MEN
ARE SOMETIMES CALLED "TINY"?

03:39.110 --> 03:41.510
[ CHUCKLES ]

03:43.390 --> 03:45.312
THAT'S FOR SAVING MY LIFE.

03:45.320 --> 03:47.959
WHAT DO I HAVE TO DO
FOR A PIE?

03:47.960 --> 03:49.427
I'M KIDDING.

03:49.430 --> 03:51.557
THEY'RE GREAT. THAN KS.

03:51.560 --> 03:56.259
BUT I'M NOT SURE WHAT I DID
QUALIFIES AS LIFESAVING.

03:56.270 --> 03:57.919
SURE, IT DOES.

03:57.930 --> 03:59.534
WELL, THAN KS.

03:59.540 --> 04:01.895
I KIND OF HAVE TO
GET BACK TO --

04:01.900 --> 04:03.606
SO, YOU ARE MAD.

04:03.610 --> 04:05.464
I KNEW THAT
THINGS WERE GONNA BE WEIRD

04:05.470 --> 04:08.030
BECAUSE OF THAT STUFF
WITH OUR DADS.

04:08.040 --> 04:10.179
I'M NOT MAD, GIA.
I'M JUST TRYING TO STUDY.

04:10.180 --> 04:13.411
WE SHOULD STUDY
FOR THE HEALTH FINAL TOGETHER.

04:13.420 --> 04:16.139
YOU WANT TO?
TOMORROW NIGHT, MY HOUSE?

04:16.150 --> 04:17.447
I'LL MAKE FLASH CARDS.

04:17.450 --> 04:20.613
FINE. OKAY.
TOMORROW NIGHT.

04:24.190 --> 04:25.828
WHERE'D THESE COME FROM?

04:25.830 --> 04:29.823
I SAVED SOMEONE'S LIFE.
CAN'T TALK. STUDYING.

04:29.830 --> 04:33.163
WELL, NOT ME, BABY.
I'M CRUISING THROUGH THIS WEEK.

04:33.170 --> 04:34.967
DID HE JUST
CALL ME "BABY"?

04:34.970 --> 04:36.506
[ Laughing ]
MM-HMM.

04:36.510 --> 04:38.364
I GOT MY SCHOLARSHIP TO HEARST.
MY GRADES ARE FINE.

04:38.370 --> 04:39.701
GOOD TO GO.

04:39.710 --> 04:41.701
DO YOU WANT ME TO CRY?
BECAUSE I'LL CRY.

04:41.710 --> 04:45.601
I HAVE TO ACE -- ACE --
ALL OF MY FINALS

04:45.610 --> 04:47.840
AND HOPE THAT ANGIE DAHL
CHOKES ON ONE OF HERS,

04:47.850 --> 04:50.739
AND THAT STILL DOESN'T GUARANTEE
ME THE KANE SCHOLARSHIP.

04:50.750 --> 04:53.913
DO YOU KNOW HOW LONG
I'VE WANTED TO GO TO STANFORD?

04:53.920 --> 04:54.852
SINCE MIDDLE SCHOOL.

04:54.860 --> 04:56.657
ELEMENTARY,
MY DEAR WALLACE.

04:56.660 --> 05:00.448
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA HOW LONG
I'VE WAITED TO SAY THAT?

05:00.460 --> 05:02.394
IT'S SO FUNNY
THAT YOU'RE WORKING SO HARD

05:02.400 --> 05:04.595
TO GO TO STANFORD
WITH ANGIE DAHL,

05:04.600 --> 05:07.034
WHEN WALLACE, MAC, AND YOUR DAD
WILL ALL BE IN NEPTUNE.

05:07.040 --> 05:11.409
SAID THE GIRL WHO'S LEAVING
ALL THIS TO GO TO FRANCE.

05:11.410 --> 05:14.607
AH, DO YOU SEE A PLANE TICKET
IN MY HAND?

05:15.340 --> 05:16.500
[ LAUGHS ]

05:16.510 --> 05:18.239
SERIOUSLY.
YOU MIGHT STAY?

05:18.250 --> 05:19.774
WITH DAD'S
STILL IN THIS MESS...

05:19.780 --> 05:22.044
COULD YOU GUYS
TONE DOWN THE ADORABLE?

05:22.050 --> 05:24.484
WESTERN CIV.
ISN'T GONNA LEARN ITSELF.

05:24.490 --> 05:26.378
I'M GONNA NEED MILK
WITH THOSE CUPCAKES.

05:26.390 --> 05:27.652
ANYONE WANT ANYTHING?

05:27.660 --> 05:30.026
UH, PEACE,
WITH A SIDE OF QUIET?

05:30.030 --> 05:32.282
[ CHUCKLES ]

05:32.290 --> 05:34.099
SHE --

05:34.100 --> 05:35.692
Shh.

05:37.270 --> 05:39.659
[ FOOTSTEPS APPROACH ]

05:41.270 --> 05:42.669
VERONICA.

05:44.110 --> 05:45.964
GOT A MINUTE?

05:45.970 --> 05:47.870
NOT REALLY.

05:51.810 --> 05:53.812
I NEED YOUR HELP
WITH SOMETHING.

05:53.820 --> 05:56.812
OKAY. THIS IS A LITTLE WEIRD
FOR ME, YOU KNOW?

05:56.820 --> 05:58.617
IS THIS GONNA
MAKE ME NAUSEOUS?

05:58.620 --> 06:01.612
I NEED YOUR HELP WITH,
YOU KNOW, ALGEBRA.

06:01.620 --> 06:04.828
LIKE, THE MATH?

06:04.830 --> 06:07.924
TO PASS THIS YEAR, I NEED TO GET
AT LEAST A "B" ON THE FINAL.

06:07.930 --> 06:09.795
I DON'T PASS,
I DON'T GRADUATE.

06:09.800 --> 06:12.121
MY GRANDMOTHER WANTS TO SEE ME
WALK ACROSS THAT STAGE

06:12.130 --> 06:13.563
AT GRADUATION.

06:13.570 --> 06:16.869
AND NOW, WITH HER BEING SICK
AND EVERYTHING --

06:16.870 --> 06:19.805
I WISH I COULD HELP,
BUT I CAN'T.

06:19.810 --> 06:22.973
I'M SWAMPED
WITH MY OWN FINALS.

06:22.980 --> 06:24.504
YEAH.

06:24.510 --> 06:27.343
ALL RIGHT.

06:27.350 --> 06:28.817
SORRY.

06:33.260 --> 06:35.251
[ GUNSHOTS ]

06:35.260 --> 06:36.989
[ SCREAMING ]

06:43.000 --> 06:47.130
LOOK AT THIS!
YOU'RE LIKE ANIMALS!

06:50.740 --> 06:54.130
SOMEBODY'S GOT TO
CLEAN THIS UP, YOU KNOW.

06:54.810 --> 06:59.713
BUT NOT ME.
THAT'S RIGHT. THEY FIRED ME.

06:59.720 --> 07:01.244
I GUESS I'M GOOD ENOUGH
TO DRIVE

07:01.250 --> 07:04.549
AN ARMORED TROOP-TRANSPORT
TRUCK THROUGH TIKRIT,

07:04.550 --> 07:07.087
BUT NOT TO POLISH THE FLOORS
AT NEPTUNE HIGH!

07:08.490 --> 07:10.981
HEY, ANYBODY WANT TO
CUT OUT OF HERE?

07:10.990 --> 07:12.992
I MIGHT TRY
TO JUMP SNAKE CANYON.

07:13.000 --> 07:16.322
WHO WANTS TO GO FOR A RIDE?
WHAT, NO ONE?

07:16.330 --> 07:19.458
WHERE'S MY GIRL? HUH?

07:19.470 --> 07:21.233
G-G-G-GIA!

07:21.240 --> 07:22.935
[ CHUCKLES ]

07:24.810 --> 07:26.266
HEY.

07:26.270 --> 07:28.170
WHO ARE YOU CALLING?

07:28.180 --> 07:29.602
NO ONE.

07:29.610 --> 07:32.841
I SAID,
"WHO ARE YOU CALLING?!"

07:34.220 --> 07:35.744
DON'T CRY.

07:54.170 --> 07:55.865
[ SCREAMS ]

08:01.340 --> 08:02.944
[ GUNSHOT ]

08:16.730 --> 08:20.359
* A LONG TIME AGO,
WE USED TO BE FRIENDS *

08:20.360 --> 08:26.026
* BUT I HAVEN'T THOUGHT OF YOU
LATELY AT ALL *

08:26.740 --> 08:28.833
* COME ON, NOW, SUGAR *

08:28.840 --> 08:31.365
* BRING IT ON, BRING IT ON,
YEAH *

08:31.370 --> 08:34.908
* JUST REMEMBER ME WHEN *

08:34.910 --> 08:39.745
* WE USED TO BE FRIENDS
A LONG TIME AGO *

08:39.750 --> 08:42.014
* WE USED TO BE FRIENDS *

08:42.020 --> 08:45.547
-- Captions by VITAC --
www.vitac.com

08:49.590 --> 08:52.024
THOMAS DOHANIC, OR "LUCKY,"
AS HE WAS KNOWN,

08:52.030 --> 08:54.351
WAS A VERY DISTURBED YOUNG MAN.

08:54.360 --> 08:56.828
I'VE LEARNED
FROM OUR SHERIFF'S DEPARTMENT

08:56.830 --> 08:59.196
THAT HE JUST COMPLETED
A TOUR IN IRAQ.

08:59.200 --> 09:01.839
IS IT TRUE THE GUN HE HAD
WAS FILLED WITH BLANKS?

09:01.840 --> 09:03.603
YES.
THAT HAS BEEN CONFIRMED.

09:03.610 --> 09:05.669
HE WAS ARRESTED
FOR STALKING YOUR FAMILY.

09:05.670 --> 09:08.571
WHAT WAS YOUR RELATIONSHIP
WITH MR. DOHANIC?

09:08.580 --> 09:10.138
HONESTLY,
WE DIDN'T REALLY HAVE ONE.

09:10.150 --> 09:12.209
HE WAS A BAT BOY FOR THE SHARKS
BACK IN HIS TEENS.

09:12.210 --> 09:14.770
WE HAD TO LET HIM GO
AFTER SOME OF THE PLAYERS

09:14.780 --> 09:16.748
COMPLAINED
ABOUT HIS JOB PERFORMANCE.

09:16.750 --> 09:18.945
WHY DO YOU THINK
HE TOOK THE GUN TO SCHOOL?

09:18.950 --> 09:20.781
WAS HE LOOKING
FOR YOUR DAUGHTER?

09:20.790 --> 09:22.314
I DON'T KNOW.

09:22.320 --> 09:24.220
I DOUBT WE'LL EVER
BE ABLE TO MAKE SENSE

09:24.230 --> 09:26.949
OUT OF THE ACTIONS
OF SUCH A TROUBLED PERSON.

09:26.960 --> 09:29.758
LOOK AT THAT.
HIS EYES ARE TURNING BROWN.

09:29.770 --> 09:31.522
[ TV TURNS OFF ]

09:31.530 --> 09:33.964
I'M THINKING
ABOUT GETTING YOU

09:33.970 --> 09:36.962
SOME SORT
OF GIANT HAMSTER BALL

09:36.970 --> 09:40.076
SO YOU CAN ROLL EVERYWHERE
IN THIS PROTECTIVE SPHERE.

09:40.080 --> 09:42.674
IT WOULD JUST
DRAW ATTENTION TO ME.

09:42.680 --> 09:47.674
NOBODY LIKES A BLONDE
IN A HAMSTER BALL.

09:47.680 --> 09:50.080
SO, I GOT
INTO LUCKY'S APARTMENT.

09:50.090 --> 09:52.217
HE SENT A WHOLE BUNCH OF E-MAILS
TO WOODY,

09:52.220 --> 09:54.552
ALL FROM
DIFFERENT E-MAIL ADDRESSES.

09:54.560 --> 09:55.959
WHAT DID THEY SAY?
NOTHING.

09:55.960 --> 09:57.723
THERE WERE ATTACHMENTS.

09:57.730 --> 09:59.948
LUCKY TRASHED
THE ORIGINAL FILES.

09:59.960 --> 10:02.724
I'M HOPING I'LL BE ABLE TO
GET AHOLD OF THEM AT WOODY'S.

10:02.730 --> 10:04.197
YOU REALLY THINK WOODY

10:04.200 --> 10:07.590
WOULD KEEP THREATENING E-MAILS
IN HIS INBOX?

10:07.600 --> 10:10.034
THE WAY E-MAIL WORKS
ON YOUR STANDARD POP ACCOUNT,

10:10.040 --> 10:12.804
THE E-MAIL REMAINS ON THE SERVER
FOR A PERIOD OF TIME --

10:12.810 --> 10:15.176
MAYBE A WEEK,
A MONTH, LONGER.

10:15.180 --> 10:17.842
AND THEN WHEN YOU LOG ON
TO YOUR E-MAIL APPLICATION,

10:17.850 --> 10:19.340
THE MAIL IS PULLED DOWN.

10:19.350 --> 10:22.012
IF YOU DON'T WANT
PEOPLE TO SEE IT, YOU DELETE IT.

10:22.020 --> 10:24.443
BUT THE E-MAIL
STILL EXISTS ON THE SERVER.

10:24.450 --> 10:27.783
SO, ALL ONE HAS TO DO
IS FIND A SELDOM-USED COMPUTER

10:27.790 --> 10:29.314
AND HOPE THAT THAT COMPUTER

10:29.320 --> 10:31.982
HASN'T DOWNLOADED
THE INCRIMINATING E-MAIL YET.

10:31.990 --> 10:34.322
AND WOODY MUST HAVE
SIX NETWORK COMPUTERS

10:34.330 --> 10:35.558
IN THAT HOUSE OF HIS.

10:35.560 --> 10:37.721
SO IF YOU HAVE
HIS PASSWORD...

10:37.730 --> 10:39.322
WHICH I DO.

10:39.330 --> 10:41.890
I LOOKED OVER HIS SHOULDER ONCE
WHEN HE WAS SIGNING ON.

10:41.900 --> 10:44.903
HE SHOULD KNOW. YOU NEVER LOG IN
WITH A MARS NEARBY.

10:44.910 --> 10:46.935
WOODY'S GOT A SHARKS DINNER
TOMORROW NIGHT --

10:46.940 --> 10:48.874
A TABLE RESERVED
FOR THE GOODMAN FAMILY.

10:48.880 --> 10:50.438
THE COAST SHOULD BE CLEAR.

10:50.450 --> 10:51.872
ACTUALLY, IT WON'T BE.

10:51.880 --> 10:55.338
GIA IS HAVING
HER NUMBER-ONE STUDY BUDDY OVER.

10:55.350 --> 10:58.239
SO...

10:58.250 --> 10:59.410
VERONICA.

10:59.420 --> 11:01.718
WHY SHOULD YOU BREAK IN
WHEN I'M INVITED?

11:01.720 --> 11:03.381
WOODY WILL BE AT THE DINNER.

11:03.390 --> 11:06.029
AND WE BOTH KNOW...

11:06.030 --> 11:10.660
IF IT CAME DOWN TO IT,
I COULD TAKE GIA.

11:11.600 --> 11:12.999
THE PASSWORD.

11:14.170 --> 11:15.239
GIVE IT.

11:15.240 --> 11:19.131
YOU'LL REMEMBER IT.
IT'S "MR. GOODWOOD."

11:19.140 --> 11:23.008
UGH. I'M SO
NOT TOUCHING HIS KEYBOARD.

11:23.010 --> 11:26.343
WALLACE LITERALLY
SAILED OVER THE TABLE. SAILED.

11:26.350 --> 11:29.717
THEN HE JUST SLAMS
INTO THIS GUY, JUST LIKE, "BAM!"

11:29.720 --> 11:31.711
AND TACKLES HIM
TO THE GROUND.

11:31.720 --> 11:33.256
THANK GOD HE WAS THERE.

11:33.260 --> 11:38.357
HE WAS PRETTY FREAKED OUT AFTER,
BUT HE'S DOING OKAY NOW.

11:38.360 --> 11:40.624
[ SIGHS ]

11:40.630 --> 11:42.154
WHAT?

11:42.160 --> 11:44.299
I'M THE ONE WHO'S SUPPOSED TO
KEEP YOU SAFE.

11:44.300 --> 11:46.222
I'M SUPPOSED TO
MAKE YOUR LIFE EASIER,

11:46.230 --> 11:48.892
AND I'VE --
I'VE MADE IT A CIRCUS.

11:48.900 --> 11:52.609
[ Laughing ] OKAY,
NO MORE PAIN-KILLERS FOR YOU.

11:52.610 --> 11:55.602
HEY,
YOU'RE OUT OF YOUR MIND.

11:55.610 --> 11:57.874
MY LIFE IS NOT A CIRCUS.

11:57.880 --> 12:01.145
NO, IT'S THE BEST
IT'S EVER BEEN.

12:15.530 --> 12:16.758
HELLO, SON.

12:16.770 --> 12:18.021
IF YOU WOULD HAVE
GIVEN LILLY

12:18.030 --> 12:19.668
THE PERFORMANCE
YOU GAVE TODAY,

12:19.670 --> 12:21.194
SHE MIGHT HAVE
GIVEN YOU THE OSCAR.

12:21.200 --> 12:24.408
I WANTED TO TALK TO YOU
BEFORE YOU TESTIFY.

12:24.410 --> 12:28.107
WE KNOW THE D.A.'s GONNA ASK
WHAT YOU SAW ON THOSE TAPES.

12:28.110 --> 12:30.476
I THINK IT'S
IN YOUR BEST INTEREST

12:30.480 --> 12:32.277
THAT YOU DON'T TELL HIM.

12:32.280 --> 12:35.113
BECAUSE I WANT SO DESPERATELY
FOR YOU TO BE FREE

12:35.120 --> 12:37.008
SO WE CAN
BE A FAMILY AGAIN?

12:37.020 --> 12:39.443
LOGAN, THE MOMENT THAT YOU SAY
YOU SAW THOSE TAPES,

12:39.450 --> 12:42.681
YOU WILL BE ADMITTING
TO DESTROYING STATE'S EVIDENCE.

12:42.690 --> 12:45.022
I'M GONNA WIN THIS, SON.

12:45.030 --> 12:47.419
AND THERE'S NO SENSE IN
YOU BEING CONVICTED OF A FELONY.

12:47.430 --> 12:51.059
OH, GEE, DAD, YOU'RE ALWAYS
LOOKING OUT FOR ME.

12:52.470 --> 12:54.495
THANKS FOR THE ADVICE.

13:13.420 --> 13:15.615
I DON'T KNOW.

13:15.620 --> 13:18.623
HEY, CASSIDY.
WHO'S AMBER?

13:18.630 --> 13:20.598
I HAVE NO IDEA.

13:20.600 --> 13:22.227
THEY KEYED THE WRONG CAR?

13:22.230 --> 13:25.222
HOW'S AMBER GONNA KNOW
THAT SHE'S A BITCH?

13:25.230 --> 13:28.233
DO YOU KNOW HOW MUCH
THIS IS GONNA COST TO FIX,

13:28.240 --> 13:30.800
NOT TO MENTION
HOW LONG IT'S GONNA TAKE?

13:30.810 --> 13:32.505
HEY, VERONICA.

13:32.510 --> 13:35.377
HEY. . .YOU.

13:35.380 --> 13:36.972
HART.

13:36.980 --> 13:39.642
I HAVEN'T SAID A THING.

13:39.650 --> 13:41.572
GOOD FOR YOU.

13:43.550 --> 13:44.687
BEAV.

13:45.290 --> 13:48.487
I THINK I KNOW SOMEONE
WHO CAN HELP YOU.

13:48.490 --> 13:51.755
FINALS ARE SO STUPID.
WE ALREADY LEARNED THIS STUFF.

13:51.760 --> 13:54.297
WHY DO WE HAVE TO TRY
AND LEARN IT ALL OVER AGAIN?

13:54.300 --> 13:56.427
YOU KNOW
WHAT WE SHOULD DO?

13:56.430 --> 13:57.522
TAKE A BREAK?

13:57.530 --> 13:59.293
I WAS THINKING MORE,
TAKE A PRACTICE TEST.

13:59.300 --> 14:01.939
THE COMPANY THAT DOES
THE TEXTBOOK HAS ONE ONLINE.

14:01.940 --> 14:04.158
[ SIGHS ]

14:04.170 --> 14:06.502
YOU'RE REALLY A GOOD STUDENT,
VERONICA.

14:06.510 --> 14:08.137
IT'S KIND OF SWEET.

14:08.910 --> 14:10.673
OH, MY GOD.

14:10.680 --> 14:12.238
IT DOESN'T LOOK THAT BAD.

14:12.250 --> 14:15.310
NO, I'M ON myspace, AND I USED
TO HAVE A THOUSAND FRIENDS,

14:15.320 --> 14:19.313
AND SUDDENLY, FOR SOME REASON,
NOW I ONLY HAVE 900-SOMETHING.

14:22.660 --> 14:26.426
[ KEYS CLACKING ]

14:26.430 --> 14:28.751
OH, DAMN IT.

14:28.760 --> 14:30.091
WHAT?

14:30.100 --> 14:31.362
MY COMPUTER JUST CRASHED.

14:31.370 --> 14:33.759
IS THERE ANOTHER COMPUTER
I CAN USE?

14:33.770 --> 14:35.237
WE HAVE,
LIKE, 80 COMPUTERS.

14:35.240 --> 14:37.401
THERE'S ONE IN THE GUEST ROOM
YOU COULD USE.

14:39.110 --> 14:43.069
NO MORE CYBER-FRIENDS, GIA.
HEALTH TEST.

15:10.740 --> 15:14.972
"KILL INCORPORATION OR ELSE."

15:14.980 --> 15:17.608
OR ELSE WHAT?

15:21.980 --> 15:23.982
Man:
WE HAVE TO TELL PEOPLE

15:23.990 --> 15:25.912
WHAT WOODY DID
TO THE THREE OF US.

15:25.920 --> 15:27.512
IT'S GONNA
COME OUT SOME DAY.

15:27.520 --> 15:29.909
A COUPLE OF THE SHARKS
HAD TO KNOW ABOUT IT.

15:29.920 --> 15:31.353
THEY'LL COME FORWARD.

15:31.360 --> 15:33.123
THINGS LIKE THIS
DON'T STAY SECRET.

15:33.130 --> 15:34.449
Man #2:
DAMN RIGHT.

15:34.460 --> 15:36.519
WOODY'S A PERVERT.
HE'S SICK.

15:36.530 --> 15:40.591
WHAT HE DID TO US IS WRONG.
WE WERE JUST KIDS.

15:40.600 --> 15:43.398
[ SIGHS ]

15:45.870 --> 15:47.508
COME ON.

15:57.150 --> 16:00.085
VERONICA.
WHAT ARE YOU DOING IN HERE?

16:05.630 --> 16:07.188
HEY, MR. GOODMAN.

16:07.200 --> 16:10.294
GIA SAID
I COULD USE THE COMPUTER.

16:10.300 --> 16:14.669
I WAS TAKING A PRACTICE TEST,
AND MY LAPTOP DIED.

16:14.670 --> 16:16.695
I HOPE YOU DON'T MIND.

16:16.700 --> 16:18.531
COME ON, VERONICA.

16:23.950 --> 16:26.373
[ SIGHS ]

16:26.380 --> 16:31.511
SO, HOW DID IT WORK OUT
FOR YOU?

16:31.520 --> 16:32.248
SORRY?

16:32.250 --> 16:33.558
YOUR PRACTICE TEST.

16:33.560 --> 16:35.812
ARE YOU AS SMART
AS YOU THINK YOU ARE?

16:35.820 --> 16:37.981
I HOPE SO.

16:39.130 --> 16:42.520
I-I SHOULD GET BACK
TO GIA.

16:42.530 --> 16:43.599
MM-HMM.

16:57.680 --> 16:58.999
GIA?

17:05.050 --> 17:07.154
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

17:07.160 --> 17:09.082
I HAVE STUDY FUEL.

17:09.090 --> 17:10.523
I HAVE TO GO.

17:10.530 --> 17:14.990
I GET THESE HEADACHE THINGS,
AND I FEEL ONE COMING.

17:15.000 --> 17:17.560
IT'S THE COMPUTER SCREEN.

17:17.570 --> 17:20.892
ALL THAT SQUINTING --
IT CAN'T BE GOOD FOR YOU.

17:20.900 --> 17:22.993
HMM, WELL, THANKS.

17:23.000 --> 17:26.128
I'LL SEE YOU TOMORROW,
GIA.

17:27.710 --> 17:31.168
DO YOU HEAR THOSE VOICES
IN THE BACKGROUND?

17:31.180 --> 17:33.000
ARE THEY SPEAKING FRENCH?

17:33.010 --> 17:36.514
WE HAVE TO TELL PEOPLE WHAT
WOODY DID TO THE THREE OF US.

17:36.520 --> 17:37.919
THREE OF US.

17:37.920 --> 17:39.615
A COUPLE OF THE SHARKS
HAD TO KNOW ABOUT IT.

17:39.620 --> 17:43.181
DIDN'T IT JUST SOUND
LIKE TWO GUYS?

17:43.190 --> 17:45.055
THOSE GAPS IN THE AUDIO.

17:45.060 --> 17:48.723
I THINK ANOTHER SPEAKER WAS
EDITED OUT OF THIS RECORDING.

17:51.530 --> 17:53.339
LUCKY WAS A BAT BOY
FOR THE SHARKS.

17:53.340 --> 17:54.830
AND THAT'S
WHEN HE MET WOODY.

17:54.840 --> 17:57.331
DID LUCKY'S E-MAIL SAY ANYTHING
ABOUT BEING MOLESTED?

17:57.340 --> 17:58.705
IT'S HARD TO SAY.

17:58.710 --> 18:01.679
IT'S A LOT OF
STREAM-OF-CONSCIOUSNESS RANTING

18:01.680 --> 18:04.478
ABOUT WAR AND THE LIFE
OF A SOLDIER.

18:04.480 --> 18:06.243
IT'S HARD TO MAKE SENSE
OF HIM.

18:06.250 --> 18:07.717
I'LL HELP YOU.

18:07.720 --> 18:11.178
I WANT YOU TO GO TO BED.
YOU HAVE A BIG DAY TOMORROW.

18:12.790 --> 18:15.486
Man: DO YOU SWEAR TO
TELL THE TRUTH, THE WHOLE TRUTH,

18:15.490 --> 18:17.924
AND NOTHING BUT THE TRUTH,
SO HELP YOU GOD?

18:17.930 --> 18:20.626
I DO.

18:21.900 --> 18:27.566
MISS MARS, YOU FIND WEALTH
AND FAME SEDUCTIVE, DON'T YOU?

18:27.570 --> 18:29.060
OBJECTION.

18:29.070 --> 18:30.094
I'LL BACK UP.

18:30.100 --> 18:31.601
YOUR PAST TWO BOYFRIENDS,

18:31.610 --> 18:33.532
DUNCAN KANE AND THE ACCUSED'S
SON, LOGAN ECHOLLS,

18:33.540 --> 18:36.532
CERTAINLY FIT THAT DESCRIPTION,
DO THEY NOT?

18:36.540 --> 18:37.677
THEY DO.

18:37.680 --> 18:40.740
AND LILLY KANE
WAS YOUR BEST FRIEND.

18:40.750 --> 18:41.774
YES.

18:41.780 --> 18:43.145
YOU LOOKED UP TO HER.

18:43.150 --> 18:44.583
YES.

18:44.590 --> 18:45.909
EMULATED HER?

18:45.920 --> 18:47.478
TO A DEGREE.

18:47.490 --> 18:49.185
IS THAT WHY YOU
PROPOSITIONED MR. ECHOLLS

18:49.190 --> 18:52.284
UPON DISCOVERING THE TAPE
OF LILLY AND MY CLIENT KISSING?

18:52.790 --> 18:57.261
YOU MEAN NAKED KISSING
WITH AARON ON TOP GYRATING?

18:57.270 --> 18:58.669
THAT TAPE?

18:58.670 --> 19:00.831
YOU FOUND MR. ECHOLLS
AT THE KANE PARTY,

19:00.840 --> 19:04.003
AND YOU TOLD HIM THAT
YOU'D GIVE HIM BACK THE TAPES,

19:04.010 --> 19:05.409
BUT HE HAD TO EARN THEM.

19:05.410 --> 19:07.537
WHAT EXACTLY
DID YOU MEAN BY "EARN"?

19:07.540 --> 19:11.544
I NEVER SAID THAT. I DIDN'T
PROPOSITION MR. ECHOLLS.

19:11.550 --> 19:13.575
HE HID IN MY BACKSEAT.

19:13.580 --> 19:15.218
[ SIGHS ]

19:15.220 --> 19:19.884
MISS MARS,
YOU'RE HOW OLD?

19:19.890 --> 19:21.152
18.

19:21.160 --> 19:22.855
YOU'RE CURRENTLY
COMPLETING TREATMENT

19:22.860 --> 19:25.420
FOR A SEXUALLY TRANSMITTED
DISEASE?

19:25.430 --> 19:27.648
OBJECT ION.
I'LL ALLOW IT.

19:31.530 --> 19:33.020
SHOULD I REPEAT
THE QUESTION?

19:33.030 --> 19:36.261
I'VE COMPLETED
THE TREATMENT.

19:44.650 --> 19:47.244
ARE YOU OKAY?

19:47.250 --> 19:48.444
YEAH.

19:48.450 --> 19:50.941
I MEAN, YOU'RE OKAY.

19:53.050 --> 19:55.450
EVERYTHING'S OKAY?

19:55.460 --> 19:57.553
YEAH, I'M FINE.

19:57.560 --> 19:59.380
OKAY.

20:02.860 --> 20:07.661
SHERIFF, JUDGE FERRIS
WANTS TO SEE YOU A.S.A.P.

20:07.670 --> 20:08.796
[ LAUGHS ]

20:08.800 --> 20:09.789
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

20:09.800 --> 20:11.358
YOU WANTED TO SEE ME,
JUDGE?

20:11.370 --> 20:12.860
THERE'S BEEN A DEVELOPMENT,
SHERIFF.

20:12.870 --> 20:15.577
IT SEEMS MR. LOBO WAS STRUCK
BY A BOLT OF LIGHTNING.

20:15.580 --> 20:17.002
WHAT, THAT HE COULD CASH

20:17.010 --> 20:18.739
OLD LADIES'
SOCIAL SECURITY CHECKS HIMSELF

20:18.750 --> 20:20.513
AND GET RID
OF THE SLOT MACHINES?

20:20.520 --> 20:22.818
I WAS WITH TERRENCE COOK
AT THE TIME OF THE BUS CRASH.

20:22.820 --> 20:24.947
THERE'S NO WAY
HE COULD BE RESPONSIBLE

20:24.950 --> 20:26.178
FOR KILLING THOSE KIDS.

20:26.190 --> 20:27.885
ARE YOU SURE
YOU DON'T WANT TO TAKE

20:27.890 --> 20:29.881
ANOTHER COUPLE MONTHS
TO THINK IT OVER?

20:29.890 --> 20:31.983
MY MEMORY ISN'T
WHAT IT USED TO BE.

20:31.990 --> 20:35.357
BUT I WAS WATCHING THIS
NATURE PROGRAM ABOUT SHARKS,

20:35.360 --> 20:36.896
AND I THOUGHT, "SHARKS.

20:36.900 --> 20:39.562
MY FRIEND TERRENCE COOK PLAYED
FOR THE SHARKS."

20:39.570 --> 20:41.891
AND I REALIZED
I HAVEN'T SEEN HIM SINCE...

20:41.900 --> 20:45.165
WELL, THAT'S WHEN I WENT AND
CHECKED MY APPOINTMENT CALENDAR

20:45.170 --> 20:48.037
AND SAW IT WAS THE DAY
OF THAT TERRIBLE ACCIDENT.

20:48.040 --> 20:50.645
IF MR. LOBO TAKES THE STAND,
THE JURY WILL FIND OUT

20:50.650 --> 20:51.969
ABOUT HIS...DEALINGS.

20:51.980 --> 20:54.642
HOWEVER, THE JURY
MIGHT BE MORE INCLINED

20:54.650 --> 20:57.380
TO BELIEVE EITHER
MY CORPORATE ATTORNEY

20:57.390 --> 20:59.210
OR MY CHIEF
FINANCIAL OFFICER.

20:59.220 --> 21:03.350
THEY WERE ALSO WITH MR. COOK
ON THE NIGHT IN QUESTION.

21:04.430 --> 21:06.386
[ SIGHS ]

21:06.390 --> 21:08.392
THIS IS POINTLESS.

21:08.400 --> 21:09.924
[ SIGHS ]
NO, OKAY, LOOK.

21:09.930 --> 21:11.818
SO, YOU KNOW
QUADRATIC EQUATIONS, RIGHT?

21:11.830 --> 21:14.162
DO I LOOK LIKE SOMEONE
WHO KNOWS QUADRATIC EQUATIONS?

21:14.170 --> 21:16.661
I'M JUST TRYING TO SEE
WHAT YOU ALREADY KNOW.

21:16.670 --> 21:19.059
ZERO. YOU WANT YOUR CAR FIXED?
TEACH ME.

21:19.070 --> 21:20.606
OKAY. OKAY.

21:20.610 --> 21:23.340
ALL RIGHT, WHAT DO YOU THINK
THAT WE SHOULD DO FIRST?

21:23.350 --> 21:26.547
AM I A 5-YEAR-OLD GIRL?
HUH?

21:26.550 --> 21:29.269
LAY IT OUT FOR ME, DOG.
MAKE ME UNDERSTAND.

21:29.280 --> 21:30.941
OKAY, OKAY.

21:30.950 --> 21:33.680
OKAY, SO, LET'S SAY
THAT YOU AND YOUR BUDDY

21:33.690 --> 21:36.011
WANT TO BUY A 12-PACK
OF A CERTAIN ITEM,

21:36.020 --> 21:38.227
SAY, LIKE, SPARK PLUGS
FOR "X" DOLLARS,

21:38.230 --> 21:40.824
AND YOU WANT TO FIND OUT
HOW MANY OF ANOTHER ITEM,

21:40.830 --> 21:43.321
LIKE, I DON'T KNOW,
OIL, RIGHT,

21:43.330 --> 21:45.321
THAT YOU CAN GET
FOR THE SAME AMOUNT,

21:48.700 --> 21:52.033
IF THIS IS YOUR IDEA OF TERMS
I'LL UNDERSTAND,

21:52.040 --> 21:53.905
I'M GOING TO KILL YOU.

21:54.680 --> 21:57.706
OR MYSELF.
IT'S A TOSS-UP.

21:57.710 --> 21:59.701
SCREW IT, MAN.
I'LL JUST CHEAT.

21:59.710 --> 22:03.214
NO, BUT...
WHAT ABOUT MY CAR?

22:03.220 --> 22:05.040
YOU KNOW POWER BUFFERS,
RIGHT?

22:05.050 --> 22:07.382
LET'S SAY YOUR DOOR PANEL
IS A SUMMER HOME,

22:07.390 --> 22:09.585
AND YOU NEED TO
CLEAR OUT THE SOUTH LAWN

22:09.590 --> 22:11.478
TO MAKE A TENNIS COURT,
SO --

22:11.490 --> 22:14.596
F-O-I-L.
THAT'S ALL IT IS.

22:14.600 --> 22:16.818
FIRST, OUTSIDE,
INSIDE, LAST.

22:16.830 --> 22:19.492
ALL ALGEBRA --
IT'S JUST THE FORMULA.

22:19.500 --> 22:21.639
NOW,
CAN YOU TEACH ME THAT?

22:21.640 --> 22:23.335
YOU'LL STILL FIX HIS CAR?

22:23.340 --> 22:25.035
THAT'S THE DEAL.

22:25.040 --> 22:29.477
OKAY, SAY YOU AND YOUR BUDDY
BUY A 12 PACK OF SPARK PLUGS.

22:29.480 --> 22:31.607
I'M JUST KIDDING.

22:33.480 --> 22:36.608
HERE'S THE QUADRATIC EQUATION.

22:40.920 --> 22:45.880
HELLO? HELLO? I'M TRYING
TO REACH RICK PICKETT.

22:47.360 --> 22:52.024
NO, RICK PICKETT.
HE'S A FRESHMAN.

22:52.030 --> 22:54.533
WELL, MAYBE YOU --

22:56.500 --> 22:57.933
[ SIGHS ]

22:57.940 --> 22:59.305
VERONICA.

22:59.310 --> 23:01.938
CAN YOU FLY TO NEW YORK,
STOP BY N.Y.U. REAL QUICK,

23:01.940 --> 23:03.373
FIND RICK PICKETT,

23:03.380 --> 23:05.746
AND SEE IF HE WAS ONE
OF THE BAT BOYS WOODY MOLESTED?

23:05.750 --> 23:08.548
Veronica:
YOU KNOW I DON'T FLY COACH.

23:10.690 --> 23:13.909
SO, THERE WERE
THREE OTHER BAT BOYS

23:13.920 --> 23:16.684
THE YEAR LUCKY WORKED
FOR THE SHARKS.

23:16.690 --> 23:18.123
TWO ARE AWAY AT COLLEGE.

23:18.130 --> 23:20.018
ONE IS BACKPACKING
THROUGH EUROPE.

23:20.030 --> 23:22.692
I'M NOT DOING ANY BETTER
WITH LUCKY'S E-MAILS.

23:22.700 --> 23:25.897
WHAT,
YOU CAN'T UNDERSTAND...

23:25.900 --> 23:28.095
"TIME IS THE TIMELINESS
OF THE PRESENT.

23:28.100 --> 23:29.362
"YOU SHOULD RESPOND.

23:29.370 --> 23:30.803
"I'VE LEFT YOU
SO MANY PRESENTS,

23:30.810 --> 23:32.960
"IF YOU DON'T FIND THEM,
THEY'LL FIND YOU."

23:32.970 --> 23:34.232
WAIT.

23:34.240 --> 23:36.401
WHEN I FOUND LUCKY IN
THE JANITOR'S CLOSET WITH GIA,

23:36.410 --> 23:38.401
HE WAS SHOWING HER A SCAR
HE GOT IN IRAQ

23:38.410 --> 23:41.072
FROM A "PRESENT"
LEFT BY THE INSURGENTS.

23:41.080 --> 23:44.481
HE CALLED ROADSIDE BOMBS
"PRESENTS."

23:46.020 --> 23:48.511
OH, NO.

23:50.160 --> 23:52.025
WOODY, WE NEED TO TALK.

23:52.030 --> 23:53.327
I'M A LITTLE BUSY TODAY.

23:53.330 --> 23:55.059
DO WANT TO HAVE
THIS CONVERSATION IN PRIVATE,

24:03.070 --> 24:06.062
YOU NEED TO CALL YOUR FAMILY
AND GET THEM OUT OF THE HOUSE.

24:06.070 --> 24:08.971
THEN YOU NEED TO CALL THE
BOMB SQUAD AND COMB THE PLACE.

24:08.980 --> 24:10.470
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

24:10.480 --> 24:11.902
THE E-MAILS
LUCKY SENT YOU --

24:11.910 --> 24:15.277
THEY REFERENCE
"PRESENTS" HE'S LEFT FOR YOU.

24:15.280 --> 24:16.542
HE CALLED BOMBS "PRESENTS."

24:16.550 --> 24:19.041
TOMMY IS DEAD, KEITH.
IT'S OVER.

24:19.050 --> 24:21.553
WAIT, HOW DID YOU...

24:21.560 --> 24:23.949
VERONICA.

24:23.960 --> 24:25.848
[ CHUCKLES ]

24:25.860 --> 24:27.748
MOST ADULTS
DON'T HAVE THEIR CHILDREN

24:27.760 --> 24:29.352
DOING ESPIONAGE WORK
FOR THEM.

24:29.360 --> 24:32.693
MOST ADULTS KEEP THEIR HANDS
OFF OF OTHER PEOPLE'S CHILDREN.

24:35.740 --> 24:38.163
YOU SHOULD LEAVE, KEITH.

24:38.170 --> 24:40.730
I READ LUCKY'S E-MAILS
TO YOU, WOODY.

24:40.740 --> 24:42.298
IT'S CLEAR TO ME
THIS IS MORE

24:42.310 --> 24:45.802
THAN SIMPLY A BAT BOY WHO
RESENTED GETTING FIRED.

24:51.320 --> 24:53.117
I'LL PUT THIS PLAINLY.

24:53.120 --> 24:56.112
YOU ARE MISTAKEN.

24:56.120 --> 24:59.089
AND IF YOU SHARE YOUR THEORIES,
SLANDER ME,

24:59.090 --> 25:00.523
I'LL RUIN YOU.

25:00.530 --> 25:02.225
I'LL RUIN YOUR FAMILY,

25:02.230 --> 25:04.221
AND YOU'LL REMEMBER THE MOMENT
YOU WALKED THROUGH THAT DOOR

25:04.230 --> 25:07.688
AS THE MOMENT
YOU THREW YOUR LIFE AWAY.

25:07.700 --> 25:10.191
I'M NOT A 15-YEAR-OLD BOY,
WOODY.

25:10.200 --> 25:11.838
YOU DON'T SCARE ME.

25:14.910 --> 25:18.141
ALL RIGHT. STAND BACK.

25:18.150 --> 25:20.300
IT'S TIME TO WATCH ME WORK
MY CULINARY MAGIC.

25:20.310 --> 25:23.211
DON'T YOU WANT TO PUT ON
A LITTLE FRILLY APRON FIRST?

25:23.220 --> 25:24.482
Terrence:
JACKIE?

25:24.490 --> 25:27.209
DAD?

25:27.220 --> 25:28.915
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

25:28.920 --> 25:33.084
THEY LET ME OUT.
YOUR OLD MAN IS A FREE MAN.

25:40.600 --> 25:41.828
I CAN'T BELIEVE IT.
HOW DID THIS HAPPEN?

25:41.840 --> 25:43.432
A WITNESS CAME FORWARD
AND VERIFIED

25:43.440 --> 25:46.864
THAT I DIDN'T USE A CELLPHONE
AT THE TIME OF THE BUS CRASH.

25:46.870 --> 25:48.428
SO YOU GET TO STAY?

25:48.440 --> 25:49.771
RIGHT HERE.

25:49.780 --> 25:51.771
I'M GONNA
LET YOU TWO CELEBRATE.

25:51.780 --> 25:53.577
CONGRATULATIONS, MR. COOK.

25:53.580 --> 25:54.911
NO, TONIGHT I GET TO HANG

25:54.920 --> 25:57.115
WITH MY TWO FAVORITE MEN
IN THE WHOLE WORLD.

25:57.120 --> 25:58.678
[ DOORBELL RINGS ]

25:58.690 --> 26:00.908
WHAT DO YOU BET
THAT'LL BE THE FIRST OF MANY

26:00.920 --> 26:04.879
"I KNEW YOU WERE INNOCENT
ALL ALONG" GIFT BASKETS?

26:06.460 --> 26:07.859
HELLO?

26:08.560 --> 26:10.323
OUT AN HOUR,

26:10.330 --> 26:13.595
AND YOU'VE SOME SWEET
YOUNG THING WAITING ON YOU.

26:13.600 --> 26:15.261
THAT'S MY TERRENCE.

26:15.270 --> 26:16.828
THIS IS MY DAUGHTER.

26:16.840 --> 26:19.809
MAYBE YOU WANT TO SEND HER OUT
FOR ICE CREAM OR SOMETHING.

26:19.810 --> 26:23.906
JACKIE? LET'S GO GET STARTED
ON DINNER.

26:27.820 --> 26:29.947
ISN'T THERE SOMETHING
YOU WANT TO SAY TO ME?

26:29.950 --> 26:34.614
"THANK YOU, MR. LOBO.
HOW COULD I EVER REPAY YOU?"

26:34.620 --> 26:35.951
AH, FORGET IT.

26:35.960 --> 26:39.157
I CONSIDER IT
A BUSINESS INVESTMENT.

26:39.160 --> 26:41.720
LEONARD, AS SOON AS
I GET ON MY FEET, I'M GONNA --

26:41.730 --> 26:44.290
[ LAUGHS ]
ON YOUR FEET?

26:44.300 --> 26:46.621
YOU FIXED A GAME, COOK.

26:46.630 --> 26:48.939
YOUR SPORT-HERO DAYS
ARE OVER.

26:48.940 --> 26:50.669
YOU'RE A SIDESHOW NOW.

26:50.670 --> 26:52.001
BUT YOU'RE RIGHT.

26:52.010 --> 26:53.671
YOU'LL BE ON YOUR FEET...

26:53.680 --> 26:57.172
STANDING AT THE ENTRANCE
OF MY CASINO,

26:57.180 --> 27:00.172
GLAD-HANDING EVERY BOZO
WITH A WALLET WHO WALKS IN.

27:00.180 --> 27:03.638
I DON'T KNOW WHERE YOU WERE
AT THE TIME OF THE CRASH,

27:03.650 --> 27:06.414
BUT I KNOW
WHERE YOU'LL BE FROM NOW ON --

27:06.420 --> 27:08.513
WHEREVER I PUT YOU.

27:08.520 --> 27:10.249
AND IF YOU WORK REAL HARD,

27:10.260 --> 27:14.253
YOU'LL HAVE ME PAID OFF
IN A DECADE.

27:22.870 --> 27:24.701
Veronica:
AFTER A WEEK OF FORCED SMILES

27:24.710 --> 27:27.679
AND THE OCCASIONAL "HEY, IT'S
TIME FOR BUSINESS AS USUAL,"

27:27.680 --> 27:29.671
AIN'T EPIC LOVE GRAND?

27:29.680 --> 27:33.047
BEEN TO ANY
GOOD MURDER TRIALS LATELY?

27:33.050 --> 27:35.371
UH...I HAVE.

27:35.380 --> 27:38.486
YOU GIVE AN EXCELLENT TESTIMONY,
BY THE WAY.

27:38.490 --> 27:41.015
IT WAS GRIPPING.

27:41.020 --> 27:43.511
I WANT TO ASK YOU
ABOUT SOMETHING.

27:43.520 --> 27:44.782
HOW UNLIKE YOU.

27:44.790 --> 27:46.428
YOU NEVER COME TO ME
OUT OF THE BLUE

27:46.430 --> 27:48.057
WITH SOME RANDOM QUESTION.

27:48.060 --> 27:51.063
DID LUCKY EVER TELL YOU
ANYTHING ABOUT WOODY GOODMAN

27:51.070 --> 27:53.937
OR THE TIME HE SPENT
AS A BAT BOY FOR THE SHARKS?

27:53.940 --> 27:56.329
NO, HE NEVER MENTIONED
THE SHARKS.

27:56.340 --> 28:00.401
BUT THERE WAS THIS WEIRD
SEMI-BASEBALL-RELATED THING

28:00.410 --> 28:01.707
THAT HAPPENED LAST SUMMER.

28:01.710 --> 28:03.746
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

28:03.750 --> 28:06.344
DUDE,
I THINK I GOT GANGRENE.

28:06.350 --> 28:08.648
YEAH, UH...

28:08.650 --> 28:10.948
SO, I NEED A KEG DELIVERED
TO THE BEACH TONIGHT.

28:10.950 --> 28:13.145
YOU KNOW,
THEY'RE DOING SOMETHING TO ME.

28:13.150 --> 28:16.950
OR -- OR --
OR I'M POISONING MYSELF.

28:16.960 --> 28:18.552
HE WAS WEARING
A CATCHER'S MASK?

28:18.560 --> 28:20.949
AND I THOUGHT THE WEIRD PART
WAS THE FOOT-BLEACHING.

28:20.960 --> 28:22.996
YOU KNOW, HE'D WEAR
THE CATCHER'S MASK A LOT --

28:23.000 --> 28:27.096
WHENEVER WE WERE
"GOING INTO BATTLE."

28:27.100 --> 28:30.866
I THOUGHT
IT WAS AN AFFECT ATION.

28:30.870 --> 28:33.100
Keith: VERONICA TOLD ME
SHE WAS ON HER WAY HOME.

28:33.110 --> 28:35.578
WHEN SHE DIDN'T SHOW UP
WHEN SHE SHOULD HAVE,

28:35.580 --> 28:38.674
I DROVE THE ROUTE
I KNEW SHE WOULD HAVE TAKEN.

28:38.680 --> 28:41.877
I SAW HER CAR,
STOPPED, GOT OUT.

28:41.880 --> 28:44.781
I HEARD A COMMOTION
IN THE BACK OF A NEARBY HOUSE

28:44.790 --> 28:46.348
AND WENT LOOKING
FOR VERONICA.

28:46.350 --> 28:47.886
THEN I WAS JUMPED.

28:47.890 --> 28:49.517
WELL,
MR. ECHOLLS TESTIFIED

28:49.520 --> 28:52.887
THAT AFTER VERONICA LOST CONTROL
OF THE CAR AND CRASHED IT,

28:52.890 --> 28:55.495
THEY KNOCKED ON THE DOOR
OF A NEARBY HOUSE,

28:55.500 --> 28:57.650
ASKED THE OWNER TO CALL
A TOW TRUCK,

28:57.660 --> 29:02.336
AND VERONICA AND AARON WAITED
ON THE MAN'S PORCH.

29:02.340 --> 29:04.001
YOU ARRIVED,

29:04.010 --> 29:06.331
SAW YOUR DAUGHTER
IN A COMPROMISING POSITION,

29:06.340 --> 29:09.002
AND STARTED A PHYSICAL
ALTERCATION WITH MR. ECHOLLS.

29:09.010 --> 29:11.672
AND THIS VERSION
HAS BEEN CONFIRMED

29:11.680 --> 29:12.999
BY THE OCCUPANT
OF THE HOUSE.

29:13.010 --> 29:14.841
OBJECT ION,
THE HOMEOWNER HAS DISAPPEARED

29:14.850 --> 29:16.272
AND,
DESPITE BEING SUBPOENAED,

29:16.280 --> 29:18.487
HAS NEVER BEEN QUESTIONED
BY THE PROSECUTION.

29:18.490 --> 29:19.889
SUSTAINED.

29:19.890 --> 29:24.259
DOES YOU DAUGHTER
EVER LIE TO YOU, MR. MARS?

29:24.260 --> 29:26.421
I'M SURE
SHE'S HAD OCCASION TO FIB.

29:26.430 --> 29:29.399
SHE IS A TEENAGE GIRL,
AFTER ALL.

29:29.400 --> 29:31.163
OTHER THAN
THE OCCASIONAL FIB,

29:31.170 --> 29:33.195
WOULD YOU SAY THAT YOU HAVE
A CLOSE RELATIONSHIP?

29:33.200 --> 29:34.497
I WOULD SAY VERY CLOSE.

29:34.500 --> 29:36.229
SO, YOU WOULD EXPECT
TO HEAR THE TRUTH

29:36.240 --> 29:40.006
ON WHAT MOST PEOPLE
WOULD CALL THE "BIG ISSUES."

29:42.210 --> 29:43.404
I WOULD.

29:45.050 --> 29:47.746
ARE YOU AWARE
THAT YOUR DAUGHTER WAS CAUGHT

29:47.750 --> 29:52.039
BREAKING INTO THE HOME
OF STEWART AND ROSE MANNING?

29:52.050 --> 29:54.086
NO, I WASN'T AWARE
OF THAT.

29:54.090 --> 29:56.558
SHE WAS ALSO NAMED
IN A DISCIPLINARY FILE

29:56.560 --> 29:57.754
OF DEPUTY LEO D'AMATO.

29:57.760 --> 29:59.159
APPARENTLY, SHE MANAGED TO --

29:59.160 --> 30:00.923
WHAT'S THE WORD
I'M LOOKING FOR --

30:00.930 --> 30:02.852
MANIPULATE HER WAY
INTO THE RECORDS ROOM

30:02.860 --> 30:03.861
WHILE HE WAS ON DUTY.

30:03.870 --> 30:05.394
DID YOU KNOW ABOUT THAT?

30:05.400 --> 30:07.595
IF YOU THOUGHT I KNEW,
YOU WOULDN'T BE ASKING ME.

30:07.600 --> 30:11.309
FOR THE COURT RECORD,
IS THAT A "NO"?
YES, IT'S A "NO."

30:11.310 --> 30:13.870
DID YOUR DAUGHTER
HAVE A PERSONAL RELATIONSHIP

30:13.880 --> 30:15.529
WITH MR. D'AMATO?

30:15.540 --> 30:16.871
YES, THEY DATED.

30:16.880 --> 30:18.199
THE COUNTY COMMISSIONER
HIRED YOU

30:18.210 --> 30:21.043
TO INVESTIGATE
THE STOLEN ECHOLLS TAPES.

30:21.050 --> 30:23.473
YOUR REPORT SUGGESTED
THAT LOGAN ECHOLLS

30:23.480 --> 30:26.483
PROCURED THE TAPES DUE
TO THE NEGLIGENCE OF D'AMATO.

30:26.490 --> 30:29.379
DOESN'T THAT STAND TO REASON
THAT YOUR DAUGHTER,

30:29.390 --> 30:32.848
WHO CLEARLY HAD THIS DEPUTY
WRAPPED AROUND HER FINGER,

30:32.860 --> 30:34.293
MANIPULATED HIM,

30:34.300 --> 30:36.097
IN WHATEVER WAY
PRETTY YOUNG GIRLS

30:36.100 --> 30:38.898
MANAGE TO MANIPULATE OLDER MEN,
ONCE AGAIN?

30:38.900 --> 30:40.561
YOU WANT TO BE CAREFUL,
MR. LAVOIE.

30:40.570 --> 30:44.006
SHE KNEW THE TAPES DIDN'T SHOW
WHAT SHE SAID THEY SHOWED,

30:44.010 --> 30:46.899
SO SHE CONVINCED
ONE "BOYFRIEND"

30:46.910 --> 30:49.231
TO GIVE THEM
TO ANOTHER "BOYFRIEND,"

30:49.240 --> 30:52.004
WHO SHE KNEW WOULD DESTROY THEM,
THUS DEFLECTING BLAME

30:52.010 --> 30:54.342
FROM YET ANOTHER "BOYFRIEND,"
DUNCAN KANE.

30:54.350 --> 30:57.114
ANY MORE AIR QUOTES, AND
I'LL BREAK THOSE FINGERS OFF.

30:57.120 --> 30:58.985
BAILIFF,
HAVE THIS WITNESS TAKEN.

30:58.990 --> 31:00.981
I'M FINE, YOUR HONOR.

31:02.060 --> 31:03.982
WITNESS CAN BE EXCUSED.

31:08.000 --> 31:10.719
OKAY, YOU PUT ANOTHER "X"
ON THAT PAPER,

31:10.730 --> 31:12.061
AND WE'RE GONNA HAVE
A PROBLEM.

31:12.070 --> 31:13.469
I'D PUT
LITTLE SMILEY FACES,

31:13.470 --> 31:16.030
BUT I DON'T KNOW
IF THAT'S GOING TO SELL "WRONG."

31:16.040 --> 31:18.702
I TOLD YOU YOU WENT TOO FAST
ON BALANCING EQUATIONS.

31:18.710 --> 31:20.337
I DIDN'T GO TOO FAST.

31:20.340 --> 31:23.434
I DIDN'T EVEN UNDERSTAND
WHAT YOU WERE TALKING ABOUT.

31:23.440 --> 31:24.577
NO SURPRISE THERE.

31:24.580 --> 31:27.048
WHAT, ARE YOU
SAYING YOU'RE SMARTER THAN ME?

31:27.050 --> 31:29.018
NO. HERE'S WHAT THAT
WOULD HAVE SOUNDED LIKE --

31:29.020 --> 31:30.840
I'M SMARTER THAN YOU.

31:30.850 --> 31:32.488
YOU DON'T REALLY
BELIEVE THAT.

31:32.490 --> 31:34.515
THEN WHY DID I GET IT
TATTOOED ON MY HIP?

31:34.520 --> 31:38.058
IF THIS IS WHAT YOU NEED TO DO
TO FEEL BETTER ABOUT YOURSELF...

31:38.060 --> 31:39.721
IF I GET YOU AN "A,"
WILL YOU SHIV HIM?

31:39.730 --> 31:41.049
HEY, I GOT AN IDEA.

31:41.060 --> 31:42.527
HOW ABOUT YOU TWO GENIUSES

31:42.530 --> 31:44.498
GO WORK OUT YOUR AGGRESSION
IN SOME COATROOM

31:44.500 --> 31:47.469
AND THEN COME BACK HERE
AND TEACH ME ALGEBRA, HUH?

31:49.400 --> 31:50.628
[ CHUCKLES ]

32:02.780 --> 32:04.611
SO, I DID A LITTLE DIGGING.

32:04.620 --> 32:08.659
WITHOUT BREAKING ANY LAWS
OR PUTTING MYSELF IN DANGER,

32:08.660 --> 32:09.979
AND I DID IT AT SCHOOL,

32:09.990 --> 32:12.220
SO YOU KNEW EXACTLY
WHERE I WAS AT THE TIME.

32:12.230 --> 32:14.653
YOU UNDERSTAND
WHY I DON'T FIND THIS AMUSING.

32:14.660 --> 32:15.922
I DO.

32:15.930 --> 32:17.898
SO WHAT DID YOU FIND OUT,
VERONICA?

32:17.900 --> 32:19.322
LOGAN TOLD ME
HE ONCE FOUND LUCKY

32:19.330 --> 32:21.230
IN THE JANITOR'S CLOSET
WEARING ONLY JEANS

32:21.240 --> 32:24.732
AND A CATCHER'S MASK
AND BLEACHING HIS FEET.

32:24.740 --> 32:26.935
THIS IS WHO THEY HIRE
AT MY HIGH SCHOOL.

32:26.940 --> 32:29.932
HE WAS WEARING
A CATCHER'S MASK?

32:29.940 --> 32:32.909
YEAH.
WHY, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

32:32.910 --> 32:35.470
I WANT TO LOOK
AT THE SURVEILLANCE TAPE

32:35.480 --> 32:36.549
LUCKY SENT TO WOODY.

32:36.550 --> 32:38.211
I THINK
I REMEMBER SEEING SOMETHING.

32:38.220 --> 32:41.109
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.
WHAT AM I LOOKING AT?

32:41.120 --> 32:42.781
IT'S A PAINTING
BEHIND THE TABLE.

32:42.790 --> 32:45.384
THAT'S A CATCHER'S MASK.

32:48.700 --> 32:50.224
INGA? KEITH MARS.

32:50.230 --> 32:52.221
I NEED YOU
TO CALL THE BOMB SQUAD.

32:52.230 --> 32:54.369
THERE'S A PROBLEM
AT THE GOODMAN HOME.

32:54.370 --> 32:56.691
WHY IS HE FILMING THE WALL
LIKE THAT?

32:58.370 --> 33:02.602
WOODY'S LITTLE-LEAGUE TEAM
WAS CALLED THE SHARKS?

33:02.610 --> 33:04.077
OH, MY GOD.

33:04.080 --> 33:06.378
I KNOW, BUT I THINK LUCKY
MAY HAVE HID A BOMB

33:06.380 --> 33:09.474
BEHIND A PAINTING
IN THEIR DINING ROOM.

33:11.250 --> 33:14.253
DAD,
YOU NEED TO SEE THIS.

33:14.260 --> 33:19.152
OKAY, BUT YOU'LL LET ME KNOW?
THANK YOU.

33:19.160 --> 33:22.493
THAT'S MARCOS OLIVERES.
THAT'S PETER FERRER.

33:22.500 --> 33:24.968
TWO OF THE BOYS
WHO DIED IN THE BUS CRASH

33:24.970 --> 33:27.621
WERE ON WOODY'S
LITTLE-LEAGUE TEAM --

33:27.630 --> 33:29.530
THE SHARKS.

33:39.950 --> 33:42.714
HOW LONG IS THIS GONNA TAKE?
THIS IS RIDICULOUS.

33:42.720 --> 33:44.449
THERE WAS
A BOMB UNDER YOUR CAR.

33:44.450 --> 33:46.987
THEY DID A THOROUGH
SWEEP OF THE HOUSE. IT'S CLEAR.

33:46.990 --> 33:51.051
YOUR STALKER
OBVIOUSLY MEANT BUSINESS.

34:01.840 --> 34:04.968
HEY, LATE NIGHT, HUH?

34:04.970 --> 34:07.939
I GUESS YOU'RE DUE
FOR A COUPLE ROWDY EVENINGS.

34:07.940 --> 34:09.498
I WAS WORKING.

34:09.510 --> 34:11.740
SO, WHAT'S THIS NEW JOB?
YOU HAVEN'T TOLD ME ANYTHING.

34:11.750 --> 34:13.775
WHAT KIND OF WORK
DO THEY HAVE YOU DOING?

34:13.780 --> 34:15.839
THE KIND OF WORK
I HAVE TO DO, OKAY?

34:15.850 --> 34:19.741
WELL, WHEN'S YOUR NIGHT OFF?
WE STILL NEED TO CELEBRATE.

34:19.750 --> 34:22.310
I CAN'T MAKE
ANY PLANS RIGHT NOW, JACKIE.

34:22.320 --> 34:24.754
OKAY, THAT'S FINE.

34:24.760 --> 34:27.627
IT'S NOT LIKE WE'RE PRESSED
FOR TIME OR ANYTHING.

34:27.630 --> 34:29.848
I'VE DECIDED
NOT TO GO TO PARIS...

34:29.860 --> 34:33.193
AT LEAST NOT
FOR A SEMESTER.

34:33.200 --> 34:34.736
I DON'T THINK
THAT'S A GOOD IDEA.

34:34.740 --> 34:37.732
I'M GOING TO BE
WORKING A LOT NOW,

34:37.740 --> 34:39.059
AND TRAVELING NONSTOP

34:39.070 --> 34:41.129
I DON'T KNOW
WHEN I'M GONNA BE HERE,

34:41.140 --> 34:43.074
AND WHEN
I'M NOT GONNA BE HERE.

34:43.080 --> 34:44.672
IT'S NOT FAIR TO YOU.

34:44.680 --> 34:46.875
BUT I DON'T MIND.
IT'S NOT FAIR
TO EITHER OF US, JACKIE.

34:46.880 --> 34:50.077
I THINK IT'S IN BOTH
OF OUR BEST INTERESTS

34:50.080 --> 34:53.186
IF YOU JUST GO TO FRANCE.

35:01.230 --> 35:03.892
WOODY'S A PERVERT.
HE'S SICK.

35:03.900 --> 35:08.098
WHAT HE DID TO US IS WRONG.
WE WERE JUST KIDS.

35:08.100 --> 35:11.536
IT'S MARCOS OLIVERES
AND PETER FERRER,

35:11.540 --> 35:13.906
TWO OF THE KIDS KILLED
IN THE BUS CRASH.

35:13.910 --> 35:16.606
I VERIFIED PETER'S VOICE
WITH HIS TEACHER, MR. WU,

35:16.610 --> 35:19.670
AND I HAVE TAPES OF MARCOS
FROM A RADIO SHOW HE DID.

35:19.680 --> 35:21.409
WOODY MOLESTED
MARCOS AND PETER.

35:21.420 --> 35:24.617
THEY WERE GONNA COME FORWARD,
SO HE KILLED THEM.

35:24.620 --> 35:26.383
BY PUTTING A BOMB
ON THE BUS.

35:26.390 --> 35:28.858
THEN HE USED THE SAME TYPE
OF PHONE-ACTIVATED BOMB

35:28.860 --> 35:31.749
ON HIS OWN CAR
TO BLOW HIMSELF UP.

35:31.760 --> 35:34.024
THERE WAS A BOMB
IN WOODY'S CAR?

35:34.030 --> 35:35.452
YOU WERE RIGHT, KEITH.

35:35.460 --> 35:37.098
YOU THOUGHT LUCKY
PLANTED A BOMB, AND HE DID.

35:37.100 --> 35:40.695
DID YOU KNOW THAT LUCKY BLEW OFF
WORK THE DAY OF THE CRASH?

35:40.700 --> 35:42.463
LUCKY IS NOT RESPONSIBLE
FOR THIS.

35:42.470 --> 35:44.961
YOU WANT TO HEAR MY THEORY
ON THE WHOLE SITUATION?

35:44.970 --> 35:47.359
YOU ARE TRYING TO GET ME
TO ARREST THE MAYOR.

35:47.370 --> 35:50.032
YOU WANT TO TURN ME
INTO A LAUGHINGSTOCK AGAIN,

35:50.040 --> 35:51.576
AND IT AIN'T GONNA HAPPEN.

35:51.580 --> 35:52.979
IS YOUR EGO
REALLY THAT ENORMOUS

35:52.980 --> 35:55.073
THAT YOU CAN TAKE THE MURDER
OF EIGHT PEOPLE

35:55.080 --> 35:56.570
AND MAKE IT ABOUT YOU?

35:56.580 --> 35:58.070
IF YOU DON'T ACT ON THIS,

35:58.080 --> 36:00.742
WOODY'S GONNA USE ALL HIS MONEY
AND RESOURCES

36:00.750 --> 36:01.682
TO DISAPPEAR.

36:01.690 --> 36:03.317
YOU WON'T BE
A LAUGHINGSTOCK.

36:03.320 --> 36:05.288
YOU'LL BE THE GUY

36:05.290 --> 36:08.657
WHO LET A CHILD MOLESTER
AND A MURDERER GET AWAY!

36:09.630 --> 36:13.225
YEAH,
THERE WAS JUST SOME FUZZ.

36:14.840 --> 36:16.990
STATIC, NO PICTURE.

36:17.000 --> 36:19.662
AND THEN I SAW LILLY,
WEARING ONLY HER BRA,

36:19.670 --> 36:22.400
SITTING ON TOP
OF SOMEONE, WRITHING.

36:22.410 --> 36:25.004
I COULDN'T SEE
WHO IT WAS AT FIRST,

36:25.010 --> 36:28.218
AND THEN THEY ROLLED OVER,
AND I SAW MY FATHER.

36:32.150 --> 36:36.689
HE CLIMBED ON TOP OF HER AND
CONTINUED TO HAVE SEX WITH HER.

36:37.890 --> 36:41.326
HE ACTUALLY SMILED AT THE CAMERA
A COUPLE TIMES.

36:42.400 --> 36:46.825
YOU'RE CERTAIN
THEY WERE HAVING SEX?

36:46.830 --> 36:47.922
YES.

36:47.930 --> 36:49.488
NO FURTHER QUESTIONS,
YOUR HONOR.

36:49.500 --> 36:51.331
YOUR WITNESS, MR. LAVOIE.

36:52.910 --> 36:56.107
MR. ECHOLLS, YOU CLAIMED
YOU DESTROYED THE TAPES.

36:56.110 --> 36:57.771
YOU ARE AWARE
THAT'S A FELONY.

36:57.780 --> 36:59.270
YES.

36:59.280 --> 37:03.239
WERE YOU GRANTED IMMUNITY
IN EXCHANGE FOR YOUR TESTIMONY?

37:03.250 --> 37:04.717
YES, I WAS.

37:04.720 --> 37:06.244
THANK YOU.

37:06.250 --> 37:08.389
NO FURTHER QUESTIONS,
YOUR HONOR.

37:18.800 --> 37:20.995
[ SIGHS ]

37:24.970 --> 37:27.165
I NEED TO TALK TO SOMEONE
ABOUT THIS.

37:27.170 --> 37:28.432
THIS BOY
THAT WAS KILLED --

37:28.440 --> 37:30.271
MY BOYS SAW SOMEONE
ATTACK HIM.

37:30.280 --> 37:33.499
THEY SAY THEY GOT
A PRETTY GOOD LOOK.

37:38.080 --> 37:42.255
YOU BOYS FEEL LIKE LOOKING
AT SOME PICTURES?

37:50.900 --> 37:53.721
CONGRATULATIONS, ELI.

37:53.730 --> 37:56.392
OH, HELL, YEAH!
[ LAUGHS ]

38:02.110 --> 38:03.702
IT WAS THIS GUY.

38:06.180 --> 38:10.116
DON...YOU GOT TO
SEE THIS.

38:10.120 --> 38:14.011
LUCKY WASN'T AT WORK THE DAY
OF THE BUS CRASH

38:14.020 --> 38:17.615
BECAUSE HE WAS IN A PADDED CELL
AT A V.A. HOSPITAL.

38:19.360 --> 38:21.180
SACKS.

38:21.190 --> 38:22.999
I'LL GO PICK WOODY UP.

38:23.000 --> 38:23.921
WELL, I GUESS YOU HEARD.

38:23.930 --> 38:25.227
ABOUT WHAT?

38:25.230 --> 38:28.666
THE ECHOLLS TRIAL.
THE JURY REACHED A VERDICT.

38:30.940 --> 38:33.329
I JUST TOOK
MY LAST HIGH-SCHOOL TEST EVER.

38:33.340 --> 38:36.673
DONE. OVER.
I'M OUT OF HERE.

38:36.680 --> 38:39.478
AND YOU DECIDED
TO CELEBRATE BY TORTURING ME?

38:39.480 --> 38:41.345
WHAT DO YOU GOT?
ONE MORE?

38:41.350 --> 38:43.011
NOTHING LIKE
HAVING YOUR FUTURE

38:43.020 --> 38:46.046
REST ON HOW MUCH YOU KNOW ABOUT
THE ASCENDENCY RULES OF BABYLON.

38:46.050 --> 38:49.656
WELL, I GOT TO GO
CLEAN OUT MY LOCKER.

38:49.660 --> 38:52.686
YOU GOT THAT SALMON
I LEFT IN THERE FOR YOU, RIGHT?

38:52.690 --> 38:55.523
YOU BETTER ENJOY THIS

38:55.530 --> 38:58.499
'CAUSE THIS IS AS NOSTALGIC
AS I GET.

38:58.500 --> 39:00.923
I JUST WANTED TO SAY

39:00.930 --> 39:04.536
IT WAS WORTH GETTING TAPED
TO A POLE.

39:06.110 --> 39:07.737
I'M GONNA MISS YOU.

39:09.510 --> 39:11.137
AND MY STUPID-ASS FACE?

39:11.140 --> 39:13.506
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

39:14.780 --> 39:19.649
I GOT TO GO GRAB MY STUFF,
THEN PICK UP MY LADY,

39:19.650 --> 39:21.379
DO A LITTLE CELEBRATING.

39:21.390 --> 39:26.851
* SLEEPING WITH THE TELEVISION
AND ALL THE LIGHTS ON *

39:26.860 --> 39:29.090
THIS CONVERSATION
NEVER HAPPENED.

39:29.100 --> 39:31.295
SURE IT DID.

39:31.300 --> 39:35.361
* BUT WE'RE BOTH ALREADY GONE *

39:37.300 --> 39:39.666
* STUCK AT THE LOST AND FOUND *

39:39.670 --> 39:43.276
* WATCH THINGS DISAPPEAR *

39:44.340 --> 39:50.813
* LOOKING FOR THE MISSING PIECE,
BUT IT WAS NEVER HERE *

40:23.680 --> 40:25.682
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

40:25.690 --> 40:28.341
AFTERNOON, MR. COOK.

40:28.350 --> 40:29.783
I'M JUST
PICKING UP JACKIE.

40:29.790 --> 40:31.257
SHE'S NOT HERE, WALLACE.

40:31.260 --> 40:34.024
WELL, SHE KNOWS I'M COMING,
SO...YOU MIND IF I WAIT?

40:34.030 --> 40:35.554
JACKIE LEFT FOR FRANCE
THIS MORNING.

40:35.560 --> 40:38.120
SHE WANTED ME
TO GIVE YOU THIS.

40:38.130 --> 40:39.666
I'M SORRY.

40:53.610 --> 40:56.613
Keith: SO, LAMB,
YOU GOT WOODY IN CUSTODY YET?

40:56.620 --> 40:59.088
WOODY'S GONE.
HE TOOK HIS PRIVATE PLANE.

40:59.090 --> 41:02.082
THERE'S NO FLIGHT PLAN
ON RECORD.

41:02.090 --> 41:04.558
Man: ALL RISE.

41:13.500 --> 41:15.639
FOREMAN, HAS THE JURY
REACHED A VERDICT?

41:15.640 --> 41:17.164
WE HAVE, YOUR HONOR.

41:22.810 --> 41:26.075
ON THE COUNT OF MURDER
IN THE SECOND DEGREE,

41:26.080 --> 41:28.002
WE FIND THE DEFENDANT...

41:29.250 --> 41:30.569
...NOT GUILTY.

41:30.580 --> 41:33.583
ON THE COUNT
